  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nCurrently, our proposer logic includes block operations when the validator is assigned to propose a block. The spec mentions there is a hard limit on the number of deposits, attestations, slashings, etc. that can be included in a block, however, we do not enforce this in our code in validator/client/validator_propose.go. Ideally, the server side methods can cap the number of items they give the proposer via RPC, and the proposer can do a simple cutoff to only include the max amount in the block.",
